<topic id="debugging-css-stylesheets">
  <title>Debugging CSS Stylesheets</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Debugging CSS stylesheets</indexterm>
        <indexterm>CSS Inspector view</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>To assist you with debugging and customizing CSS stylesheets the
        <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode includes a <xref href="author-css-inspector-view.dita"
          ><uicontrol>CSS Inspector</uicontrol> view</xref> to examine the CSS rules that match the
      currently selected element. </p>
    <p>This tool is similar to the Inspect Element development tool that is found in most browsers.
      The <uicontrol>CSS Inspector</uicontrol> view allows you to see how the CSS rules are applied
      and the properties defined. Each rule that is displayed in this view includes a link to the
      line in the CSS file that defines the styles for the element that matches the rule. You can
      use the link to open the appropriate CSS file and edit the style rules. Once you have found
      the rule you want to edit, you can click the link in the top-right corner of that rule to open
      the CSS file in the editor.</p>
    <p>
      <fig>
        <title>CSS Inspector View</title>
        <image href="../img/css_inspector_link.PNG" id="image_aqp_q11_lq" placement="inline"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p>There are two ways to open the CSS Inspector view:<ol id="ol_uqy_rl1_lq">
        <li>Select <uicontrol>CSS Inspector</uicontrol> from the <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> menu.</li>
        <li>Select the <uicontrol>Inspect Styles</uicontrol> action from the contextual menu in
            <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode.</li>
      </ol></p>
  </body>
  <related-links>
    <linklist><title>Related Information:</title><link href="author-css-inspector-view.dita#author-css-inspector-view"/></linklist>
